This paper deals with modeling and optimizing route choices in Mobility as a Service (MaaS) networks, which involves the use of machine learning and optimization techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new concept of "congestible capacity" and proposes an offline-online estimation method to capture the structural effects of flows on capacities, which involves the use of optimization and information theory techniques. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SI), Computational Engineering (cs.CE), and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
